d programs.<ref>[http://llrib.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=51&Itemid=29 About Us<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n== Governance ==\nThe First Nation elects their Council under the Custom Electoral System, consisting of a chief and 12 councillors. The current Council consists of Chief Tammy Cook-Searson and Councillors Leon Charles, Linda Charles, McIvor Eninew, Lawrence Halkett, Irwin Hennie, Larry McKenzie, Keith Mirasty, Ann Ratt, Bernice Roberts, John Roberts, Sam Roberts, and Cheryline Venne. They were elected for a three-year term beginning April 1, 2014 and ending March 31, 2017. <ref>{{cite web |url=http://pse5-esd5.ainc-inac.gc.ca/FNP/Main/Search/FNGovernance.aspx?BAND_NUMBER=353&lang=eng |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-03-02 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305165303/http://pse5-esd5.ainc-inac.gc.ca/FNP/Main/Search/FNGovernance.aspx?BAND_NUMBER=353&lang=eng |archivedate=2016-03-05 }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of First Nations peoples]]\n* [[Federation of Sovereign Indigenous Nations]]\n\n== References ==\n\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.llrib.org/ Lac La Ronge Indian Band]\n\n{{FirstNations-stub}}\n\n{{Numbertreaty|treaty=6}}\n{{First Nations in Saskatchewan}}\n\n[[Category:First Nations governments in Saskatchewan]]\n[[Category:Cree governments]]\n", "name_user": "Saxones288", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReserves and Communities", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lac_La_Ronge_Indian_Band"}
{"title_page": "Kilpedder", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name                   = Kilpedder\n|other_name             = {{pad top italic|Cill Pheadair}}\n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = Kilpedder, County Wicklow - geograph.org.uk - 1814382.jpg\n|image_caption          = Kilpedder village centre\n|pushpin_map            = Ireland\n|pushpin_label_position = right\n|pushpin_map_caption    = Location in Ireland\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Provinces of Ireland|Province]]\n|subdivision_name1      = Leinster\n|subdivision_type3      = [[Counties of Ireland|County]]\n|subdivision_name3      = [[County Wicklow]]\n|established_title      = \n|established_date       = \n|unit_pref              = Metric\n|area_footnotes         = \n|area_total_km2         = \n|population_as_of       = 2011\n|population_footnotes   = <ref>{{cite web |url=http://census.cso.ie/sapmap2011/Results.aspx?Geog_Type=ST&Geog_Code=15016 |title=Kilpedder Legal Town Results |publisher=[[Central Statistics Office (Ireland)|Central Statistics Office]] |year=2011 }}</ref>\n|population_total       = 1287\n|population_density_km2 = auto\n|timezone1              = [[West European Time|WET]] \n|utc_offset1            = +0\n|timezone1_DST          = [[Irish Standard Time|IST]] ([[Western European Summer Time|WEST]]) \n|utc_offset1_DST        = -1\n|coordinates            = {{coord|53.1136|-6.1049|dim:100000_region:IE|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|elevation_m            = 100\n|blank_name             = [[Irish grid reference system|Irish Grid Reference]]\n|blank_info             = {{iem4ibx|O268086}}\n|website                = \n|footnotes              = \n}}\n\n'''Kilpedder''' ({{irish place name|Cill Pheadair}}, meaning \"Peter's church\")<ref>[http://www.logainm.ie/?text=kilpedder&placeID=55640 Placenames Database of Ireland]</ref> is a village in [[County Wicklow]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]], located off the [[N11 road (Ireland)|N11 road]] between [[Kilmacanogue]] and [[Newtownmountkennedy]], just south of the [[Glen of the Downs]] [[Nature Reserve]]. It has a population of 1,287 as recorded in census 2011.\n\nKilpedder environs includes Glenview Park, Kilpedder Grove, Johnstown, Tinnapark, Sunnybank and the Garden Village to the south. The village has a number of services, including two [[Irish pub|public houses]], shops, restaurants and a filling station. The [[Irish army|army]] has a rifle range in the area.{{fact}}\n\n==People==\nKilpedder is the birthplace of [[Reading F.C.]] defender [[Paul McShane (Irish footballer)|Paul McShane]].\n\n==Transport==\nKilpedder is situated on the main [[Dublin]] to [[Wexford]] dual carriageway. The Kilpedder interchange, recently constructed, has improved access to Kilpedder and Greystones, and cut journey times. A permanent pedestrian bridge linking Kilpedder and Kilquade has also been completed.\n\nThe village is served by the 184 [[Dublin Bus]] route, which operates every half an hour Monday to Saturday. [[Bus \u00c9ireann]] route 133 also serves Kilpedder, operating every half an hour on peak and every hour off peak.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of towns and villages in the Republic of Ireland|List of towns and villages in Ireland]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Commons category|Kilpedder}}\n\n{{County Wicklow}}\n\n[[Category:Towns and villages in County Wicklow]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name                   = Kilpedder\n|other_name             = {{pad top italic|Cill Pheadair}}\n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = Kilpedder, County Wicklow - geograph.org.uk - 1814382.jpg\n|image_caption          = Kilpedder village centre\n|pushpin_map            = Ireland\n|pushpin_label_position = right\n|pushpin_map_caption    = Location in Ireland\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Provinces of Ireland|Province]]\n|subdivision_name1      = Leinster\n|subdivision_type3      = [[Counties of Ireland|County]]\n|subdivision_name3      = [[County Wicklow]]\n|established_title      = \n|established_date       = \n|unit_pref              = Metric\n|area_footnotes         = \n|area_total_km2         = \n|population_as_of       = 2011\n|population_footnotes   = <ref>{{cite web |url=http://census.cso.ie/sapmap2011/Results.aspx?Geog_Type=ST&Geog_Code=15016 |title=Kilpedder Legal Town Results |publisher=[[Central Statistics Office (Ireland)|Central Statistics Office]] |year=2011 }}</ref>\n|population_total       = 1287\n|population_density_km2 = auto\n|timezone1              = [[West European Time|WET]] \n|utc_offset1            = +0\n|timezone1_DST          = [[Irish Standard Time|IST]] ([[Western European Summer Time|WEST]]) \n|utc_offset1_DST        = -1\n|coordinates            = {{coord|53.1136|-6.1049|dim:100000_region:IE|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|elevation_m            = 100\n|blank_name             = [[Irish grid reference system|Irish Grid Reference]]\n|blank_info             = {{iem4ibx|O268086}}\n|website                = \n|footnotes              = \n}}\n\n'''Kilpedder''' ({{irish place name|Cill Pheadair}}, meaning \"Peter's church\")<ref>[http://www.logainm.ie/?text=kilpedder&placeID=55640 Placenames Database of Ireland]</ref> is a village in [[County Wicklow]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]], located off the [[N11 road (Ireland)|N11 road]] between [[Kilmacanogue]] and [[Newtownmountkennedy]], just south of the [[Glen of the Downs]] [[Nature Reserve]]. It has a population of 1,287 as recorded in census 2011.\n\nKilpedder environs includes Glenview Park, Kilpedder Grove, Johnstown, Tinnapark, Sunnybank and the Garden Village to the south. The village has a number of services: two [[Irish pub|public houses]], a shop, an organic restaurant and a filling station. The [[Irish army|army]] has a rifle range in the area.\n\n==People==\n*Kilpedder is the birthplace of [[Reading F.C.]] defender [[Paul McShane (Irish footballer)|Paul McShane]].\n\n==Transport==\nKilpedder is situated on the main [[Dublin]] to [[Wexford]] dual carriageway. The Kilpedder interchange, recently constructed, has improved access to Kilpedder and Greystones, and cut journey times. A permanent pedestrian bridge linking Kilpedder and Kilquade has also been completed.\n\nThe village is served by the 184 [[Dublin Bus]] route, which operates every half an hour Monday to Saturday. [[Bus \u00c9ireann]] route 133 also serves Kilpedder, operating every half an hour on peak and every hour off peak.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of towns and villages in the Republic of Ireland|List of towns and villages in Ireland]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Commons category|Kilpedder}}\n\n{{County Wicklow}}\n\n[[Category:Towns and villages in County Wicklow]]\n", "name_user": "Guliolopez", "label": "safe", "comment": "ce", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kilpedder"}
